{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.30",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 30,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 30",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 30 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:1",
      "text": "But now the younger in time scorn me, whose fathers I would not have set with the dogs of my flock:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:2",
      "text": "The strength of whose hands was to me as nothing, and they were thought unworthy of life itself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:3",
      "text": "Barren with want and hunger, who gnawed in the wilderness, disfigured with calamity and misery.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:4",
      "text": "And they ate grass, and barks of trees, and the root of junipers was their food.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:5",
      "text": "Who snatched up these things out of the valleys, and when they had found any of them, they ran to them with a cry.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:6",
      "text": "They dwelt in the desert places of torrents, and in caves of earth, or upon the gravel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:7",
      "text": "They pleased themselves among these kind of things, and counted it delightful to be under the briers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:8",
      "text": "The children of foolish and base men, and not appearing at all upon the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:9",
      "text": "Now I am turned into their song, and am become their byword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:10",
      "text": "They abhor me, and flee far from me, and are not afraid to spit in my face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:11",
      "text": "For he hath opened his quiver, and hath afflicted me, and hath put a bridle into my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:12",
      "text": "At the right hand of my rising, my calamities forthwith arose: they have overthrown my feet, and have overwhelmed me with their paths as with waves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:13",
      "text": "They have destroyed my ways, they have lain in wait against me, and they have prevailed, and there was none to help.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:14",
      "text": "They have rushed in upon me, as when a wall is broken, and a gate opened, and have rolled themselves down to my miseries.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:15",
      "text": "I am brought to nothing: as a wind thou hast taken away my desire: and my prosperity hath passed away like a cloud.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:16",
      "text": "And now my soul fadeth within myself, and the days of affliction possess me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:17",
      "text": "In the night my bone is pierced with sorrows: and they that feed upon me, do not sleep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:18",
      "text": "With the multitude of them my garment is consumed, and they have girded me about, as with the collar of my coat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:19",
      "text": "I am compared to dirt, and am likened to embers and ashes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:20",
      "text": "I cry to thee, and thou hearest me not: I stand up, and thou dost not regard me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:21",
      "text": "Thou art changed to be cruel toward me, and in the hardness of thy hand thou art against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:22",
      "text": "Thou hast lifted me up, and set me as it were upon the wind, and thou hast mightily dashed me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:23",
      "text": "I know that thou wilt deliver me to death, where a house is appointed for every one that liveth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:24",
      "text": "But yet thou stretchest not forth thy hand to their consumption: and if they shall fall down thou wilt save.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:25",
      "text": "I wept heretofore for him that was afflicted, and my soul had compassion on the poor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:26",
      "text": "I expected good things, and evils are come upon me: I waited for light, and darkness broke out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:27",
      "text": "My inner parts have boiled without any rest, the days of affliction have prevented me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:28",
      "text": "I went mourning without indignation; I rose up, and cried in the crowd.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:29",
      "text": "I was the brother of dragons, and companion of ostriches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:30",
      "text": "My skin is become black upon me, and my bones are dried up with heat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.30.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:31",
      "text": "My harp is turned to mourning, and my organ into the voice of those that weep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
